'''Associated Argentine Artists''' (Spanish: ''Artistas Argentinos Asociados'', '''AAA''') was a leading Argentine [[film distribution]] company. It emerged during the [[Golden Age of Argentine Cinema]] and was modeled on the [[Hollywood]] company [[United Artists]]. One of the first films released by the company following its creation was ''[[The Gaucho War]]'' (1942).<ref>Rist p.43</ref>

