{{Infobox organization | name = Discwoman | image = | image_border = | alt = <!— alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = Discwoman co-founders Frankie Decaiza Hutchinson, Christine McCharen-Tran, and Emma Burgess-Olson | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2014 | extinction = | type = [[Talent manager|Artist management]], [[Talent agent|Booking agency]] | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = [[US]] | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | leader_title = Origin | leader_name = [[New York City]] | leader_title2 = Founders | leader_name2 = Frankie Decaiza Hutchinson, Christine McCharen-Tran, Emma Burgess-Olson | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = http://www.discwoman.com | remarks = | former name = }}
==Biography== '''Discwoman''' is a [[New York City|New York]] based collective, booking agency, and event platform representing and showcasing female-identified ([[Ciswomen|cis women]], [[Trans woman|trans women]], and [[Genderqueer|gender queer]]) talent in the [[electronic music]] community. It was founded in 2014 by Frankie Decaiza Hutchinson (outreach, [[Public relations|PR]], and [[Social media marketing|social media]]), Emma Burgess-Olson ([[DJ]] [https://soundcloud.com/umfang UMFANG]), and Christine McCharen-Tran ([[Event management|event production]], [[Business management|business relations)]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/how-3-women-are-disrupting-one-of-musics-biggest-boys-clubs_us_56f2d797e4b0c3ef521796c7|title=How 3 Women Are Disrupting One Of Music’s Biggest Boys Clubs|last=Vagianos|first=Alanna|date=2016-03-30|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2017-03-16|language=en-US}}</ref> Discwoman's regular club nights and touring events highlight emerging and established artists from around the world,<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://thehairpin.com/2015/05/98944-2/| title = Girls To The Front: An Interview With The Founders Of Discwoman| last = 21| first = sofialuu May| last2 = 2015| website = The Hairpin| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> including [https://soundcloud.com/theblackmadonna The Black Madonna], [[Nicole Moudaber]], [https://soundcloud.com/stareyes Star Eyes], [https://soundcloud.com/sandunes Sandunes], [https://soundcloud.com/demianlicht Demian Licht], and [https://soundcloud.com/ninasonik Nina Sonik]. Overall, the collective seeks to highlight and correct the [[gender imbalance]] in [[electronic dance music|EDM]] club and festival lineups.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://femalepressure.wordpress.com/facts-survey2015/|title=FACTS 2015 – Numbers|date=2015-03-06|work=female:pressure|access-date=2017-03-16|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| url = https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2015/08/24/discwoman-and-changing-the-record-of-all-male-electronic-lineups/#5183f3712643| title = Discwoman And Changing The Record Of All-Male Electronic Lineups| website = Forbes| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Discwoman events provide a platform to feminine-identified talent by booking them at bigger venues, streamlining the growth process, and ensuring artists receive fair payment. <ref name=":0" />
==Events== Since its inaugural event at [[Bushwick, Brooklyn]]’s Bossa Nova Civic Club,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://bullettmedia.com/article/inside-discwoman-a-dance-party-by-women-for-women/| title = Inside Discwoman, a Dance Party By Women, For Women| website = Bullett Media| language = en-US| access-date = 2016-02-26 }}</ref> Discwoman has presented showcases in Boston,<ref>{{Cite web| url = https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/style/2015/04/16/discwoman-boston-celebrates-female-identified-talent/C9uXhADEgbngpF5yJwUuzK/story.html| title = Discwoman Boston celebrates female-identified DJ talent - The Boston Globe| website = BostonGlobe.com| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Detroit's Movement Festival,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://waynradio.net/wayn-features/movement-2015-girls-gone-vinyl-and-discwoman/| title = Movement 2015: Girls Gone Vinyl and DISCWOMAN| website = waynradio.net| access-date = 2016-02-26 }}</ref> Mexico City,<ref>{{Cite web| url = https://thump.vice.com/en_us/article/photos-from-discwomans-epic-takeover-of-mexico-city| title = Photos From Discwoman's Epic Takeover of Mexico City {{!}} Thump| website = Thump| language = en-US| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| url = http://remezcla.com/features/music/discwoman-interview-lucia-anaya/| title = Discwoman's Mexico City Collaborator on Using Digital Culture to Tell Women's Stories| website = Remezcla| language = en-US| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Montreal,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=30159| title = Discwoman plans Montreal weekender| website = Resident Advisor| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Philadelphia,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/entertainment/music_nightlife/Girl-power-Discwoman-dance-party-changing-the-local-DJ-scene.html| title = Girl power: Discwoman dance party changing the local DJ scene| website = Philly.com| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Pittsburgh's VIA Festival,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://www.spiritpgh.com/events/2015/10/3/via-2015-main-event-| title = VIA 2015: MAIN EVENT //| website = Spirit| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> San Juan,<ref>{{Cite web| url = http://remezcla.com/music/discwoman-tour-san-juan/| title = Techno-Feminist DJ Collective Discwoman is Headed to San Juan for Two Tour Stops| website = Remezcla| language = en-US| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> Seattle's Decibel Festival,<ref>{{Cite web| url = https://www.thestranger.com/events/22585280/discwoman-showcase| title = Discwoman Showcase at Re-bar in Seattle, WA on Thu., Sept. 24, 10 p.m. 2015 - Seattle Music Events Calendar - The Stranger| website = The Stranger| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> and Toronto.<ref>{{Cite web| url = https://nowtoronto.com/music/features/discwoman/| title = Discwoman touches down in Toronto| website = NOW Toronto Magazine - Think Free| access-date = 2016-02-26 }}</ref> The group, particularly Hutchinson, was involved in the 2017 campaign that repealed New York's [[Dancing ban|anti-dancing]] [[New York City Cabaret Law|Cabaret Law]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Witt|first1=Emily|title=Dance Outlaws Fight for the Right to Party|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/07/10/dance-outlaws-fight-for-the-right-to-party|website=The New Yorker|accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref> == References == {{Reflist|2}}
