'''Stephen Beck''' is an American artist, writer, toy designer and inventor who pioneered [[Video synthesizer|video synthesis]] and [[Video art|interactive video art]].

Examples of his work have appeared in collections including the [[San Francisco Museum of Modern Art]], the [[Museum of Modern Art]], New York and the [[Whitney Museum of American Art]].

He holds several patents in video, [[phosphene]] based display technology and energy management.<br />His writings have appeared in [[Wired Magazine]] and the [[New York Times]] and he was artist in residence at KQED – NCET for the National Center for Experiments in Television.

